## ✅ Lesson 9 — Authentication (Token / Bearer / Session) — Very Important for HPM Support Tool

In your **Philips Hospital Patient Monitoring Support Tool**, almost every API requires **authentication**.

Without authentication:

* API will return 401
* Role will not work
* Features will not load
* Device APIs will fail
* Enumerator will not work
* Config will not open

So this lesson is very important.

---

## 🔹 1. What is Authentication in API

Authentication means:

> Server checks who you are before giving access

Example:

```text
Login → get token → send token → access API
```

Flow:

```text
Login API → token → header → next API
```

This is used in almost all enterprise / healthcare apps.

---

## 🔹 2. Real Flow in HPM Support Tool

```text
UI → /login → token
UI → /features (with token)
UI → /devices (with token)
UI → /enumerator (with token)
UI → /connect (with token)
```

Without token:

```
401 Unauthorized
```

QA must test authentication.

---

